{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TTsy8rgYEGKw8jSURPWw3n","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The milestone 1 goal for this new milestones.json is: \"既存 toy プログラムのいずれかに新機能が追加され、対応するテストが全て pass する\"\n\nThe source doc says the details are intentionally undefined - the Builder should ask what feature to add and to which program. This is designed to test sefirot's question queue feature.\n\nBut I need to design something concrete. The source doc says:\n- Add a useful feature to one of the existing toy programs\n- Write tests\n- Undecided: which program and what feature\n\nSince the purpose is to test the question queue (Builder asking questions), I should design a task that intentionally has ambiguity so the Builder will need to ask questions.\n \nNow I'm considering which existing program would benefit from a new feature. I could add an `is_fibonacci(n)` check to fibonacci.py, prime factorization to prime.py, a brute force shift function to caesar.py, or an insertion position search to binary_search.py - each would be a reasonable addition that requires testing. to `prime.py`. It's a natural extension of the prime module. Since this is just one function with tests, I'll organize it as a single task in one wave. Now I need to grab the current timestamp and draft the design document.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1485,"cache_read_input_tokens":30910,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1485},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"310d8377-ec71-462e-9ae9-44ad9400a6fa","uuid":"a10c6dea-e388-409b-a675-2f353c5f6963"}
